                "display_name": "zeller",
                "accept_rate": 100
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1326831915,
            "creation_date": 1326831915,
            "body": "<p>I guess you are trying to achieve the same for <code>char[]<\/code>-s and <code>String<\/code>-s. It does not worth to write the generic method (imo, because of the lack of operator overloading in java), but you can easily convert the <code>char[]<\/code> to <code>String<\/code>(or vice versa) then execute the same code, if it is ok.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 8901244,
            "question_id": 8901109
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3e4f2561d701c8fe1bec6a7294a54624?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
